{"id":"260541113_Cauchy_Data_Contrast_Source_Inversion_Method","abstract":"This letter introduces a computationally efficient inversion algorithm based on the contrast source inversion method for two-layered media applications. The proposed algorithm employs Cauchy data to derive an integral representation of the electromagnetic field inside the homogeneous neighborhood of the target. This representation yields a Lippmann-Schwinger-type integral equation that does not involve the background Green's function. Therefore, it provides a significant improvement in computational efficiency. Numerical experiments are provided to demonstrate the performance of the method.","authors":["Ozgur Ozdemir"],"meta":["April 2014IEEE Geoscience and Remote Sensing Letters 11(4):858-862","DOI:10.1109/LGRS.2013.2280243"],"references":["253497173_Beyond_the_Born_and_Rytov_approximations_A_nonlinear_approach_to_electromagnetic_scattering","231084334_A_finite-difference_contrast_source_inversion_method","228670371_Finite-element_contrast_source_inversion_method_for_microwave_imaging","224078816_On_the_Solution_of_2-D_Inverse_Scattering_Problems_via_Source-Type_Integral_Equations","3220223_Reconstruction_of_Two-Dimen-sional_Permittivity_Distribution_Using_the_Distorted_Born_Iterative_Method","3008717_Inverse_Scattering_An_Iterative_Numerical_Method_for_Electromagnetic_Imaging","260896129_Multiplicative_regularization_for_contrast_profile_inversion","258792648_Linearized_Cauchy_Data_Inversion_Method_for_Two-Dimensional_Buried_Target_Imaging","254057872_The_Linear_Sampling_Method_as_a_Way_to_Quantitative_Inverse_Scattering","251429961_A_quasi-Newton_reconstruction_algorithm_for_a_complex_microwave_imaging_scanner_environment","246535168_Inverse_Acoustic_and_Electromagnetic_Scattering_Theory_Appl_Math_Sci","246535167_Applied_Mathematical_Sciences","231042026_Contrast_source_inversion_method","228077304_Avanced_Engineering_Electromagnetics","224440431_Microwave_Biomedical_Data_Inversion_Using_t